article.headline: Southeast Missouri State 38, Austin Peay 13
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Adam Casper returned a fumble 16 yards for a TD to help Southeast Missouri secure a 38-13 win over Austin Peay on Saturday. The linebacker also led the Redhawks (1-0) in tackles with nine. The teams were tied 10-10 at the half, but Tim Holloman, who led Southeast Missouri in rushing with 97 yards on 23 carries, scored from 2 yards out with 9:09 left in the third. Edgard Jones sacked Austin Peay's Mark Cunningham, and the ball popped right into Casper's hands, setting up his score with 8:03 left in the third quarter to give the Redhawks a 24-10 lead. Southeast Missouri put the game away with 8:20 left when John Radney scored on a 5-yard run. Cunningham was 16 of 27 with one TD and three interceptions for Austin Peay (0-1). Chris Fletcher rushed for 96 yards on 24 carries. Kevin Ballatore was 20 of 14 with one TD for Southeast Missouri.
